# Vue File Structure

## Block Order

Always use this exact block order in `.vue` files — no exceptions:

1. `<template>`
2. `<style scoped lang="scss">`
3. `<script lang="ts">` (or `<script setup lang="ts">`)

```vue
<template>
  <!-- markup -->
</template>

<style scoped lang="scss">
  /* styles */
</style>

<script setup lang="ts">
  // logic
</script>
```

## Style Block Requirements

- **Always `scoped`**: every `<style>` block must use the `scoped` attribute.
- **Always `lang="scss"`**: plain CSS is not used in this project.

```vue
<!-- correct -->
<style scoped lang="scss">

<!-- wrong - missing scoped -->
<style lang="scss">
```

## Script Block Requirements

- **Always `lang="ts"`** — plain JS is not allowed.
- Prefer `<script setup lang="ts">` for Composition API components.

```vue
<!-- correct -->
<script setup lang="ts">

<!-- wrong -->
<script>
```
